The paper deals with clock synchronization in distributed systems, which is a topic in distributed computing (cs.DC). It also involves analyzing worst-case skews and fault-tolerance, which are concepts in distributed systems (cs.DS) and control systems (cs.SY). The paper proposes a new algorithm for clock synchronization, which involves communication between nodes, making it relevant to networked systems (cs.NI). Finally, the paper deals with Byzantine faults, which is a topic in cryptography and security (cs.CR).
